<p class="ms-kicker ms-reveal">What it does</p>
<h2 class="ms-reveal ms-reveal-d1">Run repeat B2B orders without the admin pile-up.</h2>
<p class="ms-section-intro ms-reveal ms-reveal-d2">Growing wholesale teams do not just need somewhere to enter orders. They need account rules, recurring demand, special pricing, delivery addresses, stock availability, invoices, and payments to stay in sync.</p>
<p class="ms-section-intro ms-reveal ms-reveal-d2">Streamline keeps the commercial workflow connected for B2B food, bakery, beverage, commercial kitchen, and distribution teams—so the order your customer places is the same order your team picks, delivers, invoices, and reports on.</p>
<div class="ms-answer ms-reveal ms-reveal-d2">
<p><strong>What is B2B ERP software for growing wholesale teams?</strong> It connects customer accounts, ordering, pricing, CRM, inventory, fulfilment, route delivery, invoices, payments, accounting exports, and reporting in one operational workflow.</p>
</div>
<div aria-label="B2B wholesale order-to-cash workflow" class="ms-workflow-strip ms-reveal ms-reveal-d3">
